{
  "text": "Phosphorylation of EGFR on tyrosine 845 is accompanied with activation of this receptor tyrosine kinase. It is known to be responsible for oncogenetic processes [CITATION_1] and is required for the transactivation of EGFR [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Furthermore, phenylalanine substitution of Y845 (Y845F) was found to inhibit EGF-induced DNA synthesis, making Y845 a potential target in oncological treatment decisions [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "22310203",
